  "explanation": "Although the defendant is a first-time offender and has engaged in restitution, embezzlement is a breach of fiduciary duty that necessitates a custodial sentence. Given the amount embezzled and the mitigation provided by the partial repayment and clean record, a sentence of six months is proportionate to deter similar white-collar crime while reflecting the defendant's low risk of re-offending.",
  "verdict": 6
}
